Hurricane Rita was upgraded to a Category 3 after slamming Cuba and the Florida Keys. She packed a wind of 115 mph. Rita was upgraded to an extremely dangerous category 4 hurricane as it bore down on Texas. In the Gulf of Mexico Rita gained strength to a category 5 hurricane. One million people evacuated the Gulf Coast. Cuba set up 600 shelters in Havana housing 230000 evacuees. Oil companies evacuated staff from the Gulf as hurricane Rita approached, shutting down over 70 percent of US oil production in the area. 